In mathematics, '''infinitesimal cohomology''' is a [[cohomology theory]] for [[algebraic variety|algebraic varieties]] introduced by {{harvs|txt|last=Grothendieck|authorlink=Alexander Grothendieck|year=1966}}. In characteristic 0 it is essentially the same as [[crystalline cohomology]]. In nonzero characteristic ''p'' {{harvtxt|Ogus|1975}} showed that it is closely related to [[etale cohomology]] with mod&nbsp;''p'' coefficients, a theory known to have undesirable properties.

