'''Lynn Margaret Batten''' (born 1948){{r|born}} is a Canadian mathematician{{r|future}} known for her books about [[finite geometry]] and [[cryptography]], and for her research on the classification of [[malware]].{{r|malice}}

==Education and career==
Batten earned her Ph.D. at the [[University of Waterloo]] in 1977.
Her dissertation was ''D-Partition Geometries''.{{r|diss}}

Formerly the Associate Dean for Academic and Industrial Research at the [[University of Manitoba]], she holds the Deakin Chair in Mathematics at [[Deakin University]] in Australia, where she directs the information security group.{{r|wiley}}

==Books==
Deakin is the author of:
*''Combinatorics of Finite Geometries'' (Cambridge University Press, 1986; 2nd ed., 1997){{r|cfg}}
*''The Theory of Finite Linear Spaces: Combinatorics of Points and Lines'' (with Albrecht Beutelspacher, Cambridge University Press 1993){{r|tfls}}
*''Public Key Cryptography: Applications and Attacks'' (Wiley, 2013)

